# Cloudflare Pages redirects — the /bosc re-root (#307 PR 2).
# Site-specific record content (Lima) moved from the root to /bosc so future watershed
# sites are clean siblings (/gcp, …). These keep every old, deployed URL working.
#
# The network root `/` is a TEMPORARY (302) redirect, not a permanent one: it will host
# real network-level content once a second site lands, so browsers must not hard-cache it.
#
# NETWORK-GLOBAL pages stay at the root and are NOT rewritten — they're shared across every
# watershed site, so their URLs don't change: /about, /about-me, /wiki/*, /ask, /network/*,
# and the API (/api/*).

/                       /bosc/                      302
/start                  /bosc/start                 301
/timeline               /bosc/timeline              301
/submit                 /bosc/submit                301
/site/*                 /bosc/site/:splat           301
/watershed/*            /bosc/watershed/:splat      301
/docs/*                 /bosc/docs/:splat           301
/reports/*              /bosc/reports/:splat        301
/walk/*                 /bosc/walk/:splat           301
